  <primary_outcome>
    <measure>Locoregional Control</measure>
    <time_frame>12 weeks post treatment</time_frame>
    <description>To examine whether patients with locally advanced head and neck squamous cell carcinoma unsuitable for either cisplatin chemotherapy or monoclonal antibody therapy benefit from the addition of nimorazole to standard definitive radiotherapy in terms of increased locoregional control without additional serious toxicity.</description>
